Join our mission!

WashMates is an application based startup hoping to revolutionize laundry care through low pricing and high quality service.
Full Description: No matter who you are, where you are from, your background,  your heritage, we all have one thing in common. We all do laundry. Although, how we each get our laundry done does differ. Whether it be a housekeeper, or doing Laundry themselves at home or at a laundromat. A lot like what Uber has done to the transportation industry, we hope WashMates will do for laundry. Currently there is no national laundromat or dry-cleaner; instead there are dozens of different providers within each various city and state. Although the idea of centralizing laundry may seem like an obvious eventuality, but it’s not when you think about all of the barriers there are to become a laundromat and/or dry-cleaner. When it comes to laundromats, it takes a large space and a large capital investment to open dozens of facilities in every city. The same goes for dry-cleaners, except dry-cleaners, also need special licensing to use the chemicals that are commonly used in the process of dry-cleaning clothes.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: IdealStudent is a student engagement application that enables middle to high schools students to become ideal college candidates. Students can perform gap analysis to identity if their academic performance is on par, meeting, or needs improvement, and find out exactly what to focus on, when to focus, and how to track and measure their progress, resulting in a student more aligned to their college of choice.   The student engagement package includes detailed infographics with a visual overview of the various characteristics and factors that uniquely define them, a skill building timeline, and a wealth of information about college choices. Users are provided with a summary of all material in the students’ package; a page specifically devoted to assisting them with thinking about and composing their personal mission and vision statements, as well as identifying and compiling a list of their talents, passions, and goals, written in their own words; a record of accomplishments, successes, and extra-curricular activities; additional customized recommended tasks, including websites specific to their interest, recommended books and activities in their area of interest, and organizational tips; and comprehensive information on admission from selected destination colleges, including admission requirements and deadlines, early and regular admission rates, GPAs, financial aid, and more.   IdealStudent is based in Chicago, Illinois, the United States.

Description: LightLouver system helps move buildings  towards energy sustainability and LEED certification.
Full Description: The Mission of LightLouver LLC is to provide high-quality, high-performing, affordable daylighting and solar control products that reduce energy use, reduce green house gas emissions, and enhance the quality of indoor environments in new and existing buildings. The co-founders of LightLouver LLC, Michael Holtz, Donald Frey, and Zack Rogers have more than 90 years of combined experience working with the designers, owners, and operators of commercial buildings to improve performance, decrease energy use and reduce greenhouse gas emissions. Messrs Holtz and Frey were co-founders of Architectural Energy Corporation (AEC) in 1982, after having worked together at the Solar Energy Research Institute (now National Renewable Energy Laboratory) and individually with early pioneers in the solar and sustainable buildings fields. The LightLouver Daylighting System evolved from their work at AEC conducting product research and development, providing architectural/sustainable design assistance, providing daylighting consulting, and conducting building energy performance monitoring and analysis. LightLouver LLC was established in 2004 as a business focused solely on the design, development, and delivery of daylighting and solar control products. Zack Rogers was appointed the Director of Engineering. Messrs Holtz and Frey joined LightLouver LLC full time in early 2010. LightLouver LLC is concerned about the survival of the planet, the quality of life and well being of the people on it, national and local community involvement, and providing a rewarding and satisfying work environment for its employees. All component parts of the LightLouver units are manufactured and assembled in the United States of America.
